			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">6502freak wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">NewRisingSun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">the NES creates illegal colors with negative RGB values. The NTSC standard says nothing about how to treat illegal signals.</div><br />Now you have to explain how NTSC operates in RGB colour space (instead of YIQ), and what exactly are "illegal colours".</div>
<br />NTSC specifies a matrix for converting the YIQ components to RGB for display. As I understand NewRisingSun's post, an "illegal color" is a combination of Y, I, and Q that decodes to an RGB signal with one or more negative components.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

